[{"question":"Is this just another illustration as this case has already illuminated of social media completely out of control with a certain element of teenagers in America right now?","answer":"Absolutely, completely out of control.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":52,"aSentId":53},{"question":"These are the threats from the two teenage girls you have in custody now, right?","answer":"That\u0027s correct.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"What did they say that made you arrest them?","answer":"Well, one says, \"You ripped my family apart, you made my cousin cry so when I see you, (EXPLETIVE DELETED), it\u0027s going to be a homicide.\"","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"And the next?","answer":"And the next is, \"I\u0027ll celebrate by beating the (EXPLETIVE DELETED) out of Jane Doe.\"","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"Did you feel that was a significant thing?","answer":"It was -- it was a very emotionally packed moment that occurred in that courtroom where watching this young boy suffer once he realized what the punishment and what had happened at that point.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":89,"aSentId":90},{"question":"Does she feel any sense of forgiveness to these two young men that did this?","answer":"Well, she has not at this point forgiven anybody for what she\u0027s been through, the terrible ordeal.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":99,"aSentId":100},{"question":"Can you repeat that question, please, sir?","answer":"I\u0027m really asking how you\u0027re feeling today as the father of a young man who has been convicted of raping a young teenaged girl.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"Do you feel a sense of guilt, Mr. Richmond, about the fact you were not there for your son as a father for more than a very little period in his life?","answer":"Of course I feel a sense of guilt.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":122,"aSentId":123},{"question":"You must feel a sense of shame, don\u0027t you?","answer":"Well, first of all, they had no text messages for Ma\u0027lik.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":129,"aSentId":130},{"question":"But I also understand your son has been convicted of a very serious offense in raping a young woman and what I want to ask you is what is your feeling towards that young girl who went through this terrible ordeal and what is your feeling towards her family?","answer":"Well, I feel sorry for the young girl.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":162,"aSentId":163},{"question":"Did you not think that?","answer":"Well, you have about five different questions there.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":189,"aSentId":190},{"question":"Would you have advised your client to apologize for a crime he\u0027s always denied committing?","answer":"Well, his apology was for the pain that he caused.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":192,"aSentId":193},{"question":"Will you be appealing then, in that case?","answer":"There will be an appeal.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":197,"aSentId":198},{"question":"Can you stay for another segment?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":218,"aSentId":219},{"question":"What does it say about Steubenville or indeed, America and teenagers today?","answer":"Well, the judge did find that both defendants were delinquent, in other words, that they were guilty of the crime of rape.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"How do we advance this to a higher level?","answer":"I think you have to start from a position that the biggest victim here is not your client.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":318,"aSentId":319},{"question":"-- what is your view of that behavior?","answer":"Oh, it\u0027s abhorrent.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":337,"aSentId":338},{"question":"Ma\u0027lik Richmond had one text out of a day full of testimony full of text messages and e-mails and tweets which he had none, okay?","answer":"But it\u0027s not really just about the text.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":343,"aSentId":344},{"question":"How do we -- where do we go from here?","answer":"Where we go from here is we say we acknowledge if a person does something wrong, then we make amends to that person.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":347,"aSentId":348},{"question":"Oh, so you\u0027re not going to appeal from the judgment of delinquency?","answer":"I don\u0027t believe -- I don\u0027t believe he should have to register as a sex offender until he dies.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":356,"aSentId":357},{"question":"Either way, would you want to be judged for the rest of your life for something you did at 16?","answer":"Well then maybe you ought to think about that -","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":374,"aSentId":375},{"question":"Excuse me?","answer":"Wait, wait, wait.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":379,"aSentId":380},{"question":"Did you choose to make adult films?","answer":"I was a young girl.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":382,"aSentId":383},{"question":"Did you choose to make adult films and profit?","answer":"ORDS: I was a 15-year-old girl, and I don\u0027t need to apologize to you, honey.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":389,"aSentId":390},{"question":"What is the relevance of that?","answer":"Well, she\u0027s saying don\u0027t judge someone.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":392,"aSentId":393},{"question":"I\u0027m not -- did you hear me disagree with that?","answer":"OK, I\u0027ve got to leave it there.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":413,"aSentId":414},{"question":"What did you make of it?","answer":"You know, Piers, it\u0027s not shocking to me.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":434,"aSentId":435},{"question":"Are these just very unusual children that get affected?","answer":"I\u0027m glad you asked that.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":447,"aSentId":448},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"I think with this young man, you had an unbelievable recipe for disaster on so many different fronts.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":468,"aSentId":469},{"question":"But where was she with this seven foot spreadsheet of murderers, with taking him to these gun ranges all the time, feeding this tormented, weird obsessive loner mind?","answer":"It enrages me, to tell you the truth.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":483,"aSentId":484},{"question":"Is she just a cold-blooded psycho killer?","answer":"I would not like to see her out in society, if you want to know my opinion.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":515,"aSentId":516},{"question":"Very quickly, on that, of course the great debate is can somebody who is having these outrageous fantasies, really evil stuff, does that make them a criminal?","answer":"Well, you know, it all begins with fantasy.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":536,"aSentId":537},{"question":"But what did you make of her?","answer":"I\u0027m delighted she\u0027s done it, for whatever her reason.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":556,"aSentId":557},{"question":"And why don\u0027t you just talk me through what you believe caused the tragic death of this young girl?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":592,"aSentId":593},{"question":"Just from that point of view, has she been suffering since the death of Cous-Cous?","answer":"Yeah, she\u0027s been under a lot of stress.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":632,"aSentId":633},{"question":"Would you say that?","answer":"Well, I think this gives just a powerful example of really how powerful these creatures are.","docId":"130318pmt","qSentId":648,"aSentId":649}]